A '''bug''' is an insect of the order [[Hemiptera]], known as the &quot;true bugs&quot;.

'''Bug''' or '''BUG''' may also refer to:

==Biology==
* Informally, most [[arthropod]]s, except marine crustaceans, including individuals or species of
** [[insect]]
** [[spiders]]
** [[scorpion]]
** [[mite]]
** [[tick]]
** [[centipede]]
** [[millipede]]
** [[woodlouse]]
* [[Bacterium]] or any microorganism that causes illness and has a superficial resemblance to an insect, or bug, when viewed through a microscope
* Bug, a [[hybrid dog]] that is a cross between a pug and a Boston terrier
* One of several species of slipper lobster, such as
** [[Moreton Bay bug]]
** [[Balmain bug]]

==Geography==
* [[Western Bug]] River, in Ukraine, Poland, and Belarus
* [[Southern Bug]] River, in Ukraine

==Technology==
* [[Software bug]], or a software defect
* [[:Category:Hardware bugs|Errors in hardware]] with close affinity to software
* [[Covert listening device]], or bug, commonly used in espionage and in police investigations
* [[Web bug]], a technique to track who has read a web page or e-mail

==Art and media==
* [[Bug AS]], a full service production company based in Norway
* [[Bug (1975 film)|''Bug'' (1975 film)]], a film directed by Jeannot Szwarc
* [[Bug (2002 film)|''Bug'' (2002 film)]], comedy-drama about a chain of events begun by a boy squashing a bug
* [[Bug (play)|''Bug'' (play)]], a play by Tracy Letts
** [[Bug (2006 film)|''Bug'' (2006 film)]], a film adaptation of the play directed by William Friedkin
** [[Bug (2006 soundtrack)|''Bug'' (2006 soundtrack)]], the soundtrack to the film
* [[Bug (Starship Troopers)|Bug (''Starship Troopers'')]], a fictional alien race from the novel and film ''Starship Troopers''
* [[Bug (Dinosaur Jr. album)|''Bug'' (Dinosaur Jr. album)]]
* [[Bug (Dave Davies album)|''Bug'' (Dave Davies album)]]
* [[BUG (magazine)|''BUG'' (magazine)]], a Croatian magazine
* ''[[Bug!]]'', a video game
* A distinctive logo or symbol, such as a watermark-like [[digital on-screen graphic]] of a broadcaster's logo
* &quot;Bug,&quot; a song by Phish from their 2000 album ''[[Farmhouse (album)|Farmhouse]]''
* &quot;Bug&quot;, a song by Welsh alternative rock band [[Feeder]], from the album ''[[Echo Park (album)|Echo Park]]''
* Bug, a character in the Marvel comic book series ''[[Micronauts (comic book)|The Micronauts]]''
* [[Bobby &quot;Bug&quot; Guthrie]], a character in the TV series ''Life Unexpected''
* The Bug, one of several projects led by British musician [[Kevin Martin (British musician)|Kevin Martin]]

==Other==
* [[Brooklyn Union Gas]], now known as KeySpan Corporation
* A nickname for the [[Volkswagen Beetle]] automobile
* [[Bug (poker)]], a restricted wild card
* A [[holdout]] device for a card cheat
* [[Buginese language]], ISO 639 code &quot;bug&quot;
* [[Bicycle User Group]], a group set up to promote cycling issues

